-- =====================================================================
-- Tier 3 ENRICHMENT R3-G — NEW, fully-attributed TB Investigation
-- =====================================================================
-- Agent: R3-G. Block: 22029000-22029999, sub-range 22029020-22029129
-- (the rest of 22029xxx is owned by zz_lab101_unblock.sql — its UIDs are
--  22029000, 22029300-302, 22029400-402, 22029500, 22029600-634,
--  22029699-734, 22029800-801, 22029999; this fixture stays clear of all
--  of them by living in 22029020-22029129, verified unused 2026-06-02).
--
-- GOAL
--   Raise dbo.tb_datamart column coverage (currently ~277/318) by adding
--   a BRAND-NEW TB investigation that natively carries the ~41 columns
--   the existing TB anchor (PHC 22001000) leaves NULL. This is PURELY
--   ADDITIVE: every row is keyed to NEW UIDs in this agent's sub-range.
--   Nothing shared is UPDATEd or DELETEd.
--
-- WHY ADDITIVE-NEW, NOT AN ENRICH-IN-PLACE (hard lesson)
--   A prior attempt (_quarantine/zz_tb_datamart_enrich_r3.sql.generated-
--   always-violation) tried to fill the same 41 columns by UPDATE-ing the
--   shared D_PATIENT key 3, repointing the shared F_TB_PAM keys, and
--   INSERT-ing nrt_investigation_notification WITH the GENERATED ALWAYS
--   columns refresh_datetime/max_datetime (Msg 13536). It regressed
--   coverage and threw on apply. This fixture does the opposite:
--     * Authors its OWN Patient / Provider(s) / Organization(s) so the
--       dim-key resolution in F_TB_PAM / sp_tb_datamart happens NATURALLY
--       (no F_TB_PAM repoint, no D_PATIENT UPDATE).
--     * Lets sp_nrt_investigation_postprocessing create the
--       confirmation_method[_group] rows from an nrt_investigation_
--       confirmation staging row (correct runtime INVESTIGATION_KEY) —
--       no hand-authored confirmation_method_group with a guessed key.
--     * OMITS refresh_datetime / max_datetime from EVERY nrt_* INSERT.
--
-- COLUMN MAP — how each previously-NULL tb_datamart column gets populated
-- (verified against routine 255-sp_tb_datamart_postprocessing-001.sql):
--   Provider/org names (11): INVESTIGATOR_FIRST/LAST_NAME,
--     INVESTIGATOR_PHONE_NUMBER, PHYSICIAN_FIRST/LAST_NAME,
--     PHYSICIAN_PHONE_NUMBER, REPORTER_FIRST/LAST_NAME,
--     REPORTER_PHONE_NUMBER, REPORTING_SOURCE_NAME, HOSPITAL_NAME
--       <- F_TB_PAM resolves PROVIDER/PHYSICIAN/PERSON_AS_REPORTER/
--          ORG_AS_REPORTER/HOSPITAL keys by joining nrt_investigation's
--          investigator_id / physician_id / person_as_reporter_uid /
--          org_as_reporter_uid / hospital_uid to D_PROVIDER.PROVIDER_UID
--          and D_ORGANIZATION.ORGANIZATION_UID (206 SP steps 14-19).
--          255 then reads the names off those dims (steps 2-6).
--   Patient attrs (16): PATIENT_SSN, PATIENT_NAME_SUFFIX,
--     PATIENT_GENERAL_COMMENTS, PATIENT_PHONE_EXT_HOME/WORK,
--     PATIENT_WITHIN_CITY_LIMITS, RACE_ASIAN_1/2/3/ALL/GT3_IND,
--     RACE_NAT_HI_1/2/3/ALL/GT3_IND
--       <- 255 #PATIENT reads these straight off D_PATIENT keyed by
--          F_TB_PAM.PERSON_KEY (= our new D_PATIENT).
--   Confirmation (5): CONFIRMATION_DATE, CONFIRMATION_METHOD_1/2/3/ALL
--       <- nrt_investigation_confirmation -> (005 SP) confirmation_method
--          + confirmation_method_group keyed to our runtime INVESTIGATION
--          _KEY -> 255 #CONFIRMATION_METHOD_OUT (DESC len>2 to survive
--          255 line 1391).
--   Notification (1): NOTIFICATION_SENT_DATE
--       <- nrt_investigation_notification.last_notification_send_date on
--          our public_health_case_uid (255 line 1514/1528).
--   Notification submitter (1): NOTIFICATION_SUBMITTER
--       <- notification.notification_submitted_by -> user_profile
--          (255 lines 1530-1531, 1649-1655). Reached because our
--          notification_event.patient_key = our PERSON_KEY.
--   User names (2): INVESTIGATION_CREATED_BY, INVESTIGATION_LAST_UPDTD_BY
--       <- nrt_investigation.add_user_id / last_chg_user_id ->
--          user_profile (255 lines 1532-1535, 1656-1669). We point these
--          at our NEW user_profile row (NEW NEDSS_ENTRY_ID), so the shared
--          superuser user_profile is never created/edited.
--   Investigation attrs (4): GENERAL_COMMENTS, ILLNESS_DURATION,
--     ILLNESS_DURATION_UNIT, PROGRAM_AREA_DESCRIPTION
--       <- GENERAL_COMMENTS/ILLNESS_DURATION* come off the INVESTIGATION
--          dim (populated from nrt_investigation by 005 SP); we set the
--          nrt_investigation source columns. PROGRAM_AREA_DESCRIPTION off
--          nrt_investigation.program_area_description.
--   Outbreak (1): OUTBREAK_NAME
--       <- 255 joins nrt_srte_Code_value_general (CODE_SET_NM='OUTBREAK_NM')
--          on INVESTIGATION.OUTBREAK_NAME. We set OUTBREAK_NAME on the
--          nrt_investigation row to an existing OUTBREAK_NM code (looked up
--          at tail-exec; falls back to NULL if none — additive, never an
--          UPDATE to a shared code table).
--
-- TAIL-EXEC chain (bottom of file):
--   sp_nrt_investigation_postprocessing (flows our nrt_investigation ->
--     INVESTIGATION + confirmation_method[_group]); the 12 d_topic SPs +
--     sp_nrt_d_tb_pam_postprocessing + sp_nrt_tb_pam_ldf_postprocessing
--     + sp_f_tb_pam_postprocessing; then sp_tb_datamart_postprocessing
--     and sp_tb_hiv_datamart_postprocessing.
--   NEW PHC uid to add to the orchestrator PHC_UIDS list: 22029100.
-- =====================================================================

